			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A vulnerability was found in Keycloak. Deployments of Keycloak with a reverse proxy not using pass-through termination of TLS, with mTLS enabled, are affected. This issue may allow an attacker on the local network to authenticate as any user or client that leverages mTLS as the authentication mechanism. \n            STATEMENT: Red Hat Enterprise Application Platform does not ship the Keycloak server code and thus is not affected by this vulnerability.",
